This paper deals with automatic program repair, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper presents a formal framework for repairing imperative, sequential programs with multiple assertions, which involves modifying the original program. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of predicate abstraction, which is a technique used in formal verification (cs.LO) and model checking (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of SMT solving, which is a technique used in computer security (cs.CR).
